<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>AC Milan remain in talks with Tottenham for Serge Aurier and have enquired about Norwich City right back Max Aarons. </p>

<p>Matt Doherty's arrival in North London will allow Aurier to move on this summer but the club are still to receive a suitable bid for the full back. </p>

<p>The 20-year-old Aarons, meanwhile, is waiting to see if a move to Barcelona materialises.  </p>

<p>AC Milan are locked in talks with Tottenham over signing out of favour full back Serge Aurier</p>

<p>The Serie A giants have also made an enquiry over highly-rated Norwich defender Max Aarons</p>

<p>The Spanish side have been negotiating for Ajax right-back Sergino Dest but face competition from Bayern Munich and Aarons is their back-up option. </p>

<p>It was reported recently that they saw two shock bids for Aarons, including one worth £20m, rejected by Norwich.  </p>

<p>Roma are also keen on Aarons though Norwich want the same price tag guaranteed after dismissing loan offers. </p>

<p>Aarons will feature against Bournemouth on Sunday afternoon after boss Daniel Farke insisted the player hasn't been affected by the speculation.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Norwich City defender Akin Famewo has joined League One side Charlton Athletic on a season-long loan.</p>

<p>Aarons (L) is waiting to see whether a concrete offer from Barcelona is submitted this summer</p>
